[normal]The Table 1 shows that human (latent failures) committed by various stakeholder(s) organisations dominate the rare and bad event of a cyclist
[normal]’s
[normal] accidental death.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]From the partial HAZOP 
[normal]study it can be inferred that accelerating train relative to the cyclist is an occupational hazard. Because in a relative (from Albert Einstein’s perspective) universe, inertial path is greater than accelerated path or in geometric terms, the diagonal of a
[normal] triangle is more than sum of it sides is shown by Sir Roger Penrose
[normal] 
[normal](Penrose, 2004)
[normal]. These findings are counter –intuitive to 
[normal]ancient Greek (Pythagoras theorem) and 17
[normal]th
[normal] Century (Newtonian dynamics) physics
[normal] 
[normal](Reason, 1990)
[normal].  
[normal]The HAZOP Study can be applied to all other interfaces requiring a study. Similar detailed studies were performed by author and published
[normal] 
[normal](Appicharla, 2006)
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal](Appicharla, 2010)
[normal], 
[normal](Appicharla, 2012)
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal](Appicharla, 2013)
[normal].
