[normal](RSSB
[normal] Railway Group Standards are the ORR basis for Network Rail’s Operating License)
[normal]. The Railway Group Standar
[normal]ds do not specify conditions that may manifest hazards for the duty-holders. 
[normal]Accident Investigation techniques LTA (RAIB use of Haddon type of information on flow of sequence of events during pre and post-accident stages does not lead to James Reason’s
[normal] Model). 
[normal]Representations to generate and capture hazard scenarios LTA ( ORR does not use any information to inform itself of the hazard scenarios) 
[normal]Comprehension of systemic causal factors LTA (Network Rail Level Crossing Risk Assessment Mod
[normal]el does 
[normal]not capture engineering and management errors
[normal])
[normal]Awareness of Systemic Errors (biases) LTA ( Network Rail Level Crossing Risk Assessment Model does not 
[normal]any branch to model them) Risk scoring does not help hazard causal factors. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]On the question of 
[normal]safety budget for eliminating risk from level crossings, Nobel
[normal] Laureate Daniel Kahneman hypothetical argument 
[normal]against precautionary principle 
[normal]is difficult to sustain as the budget of £9 billion is insignificant in comparison to other amounts of £80 billion
[normal] Finance Loan Schemes to support house buying activity
[normal]. 
[normal]Nobel
[normal] Laureate Daniel Kahneman does agree that people do not wish to trade minute increase in risk to their health of their near and dear ones (pp350/351)
[normal] 
[normal](Kahneman, 2011)
[normal]. 
